No longer hearing Lulu breathing down his ankles, Cody slowed. He felt
a brief pang of embarrassment at having been spooked in such a manner,
but quickly shook the feeling. "After all," he said to himself,
"Master Wen might have had the same reaction himself if he was here,
and being followed by Lulu." He thought about that, then added,
"Master Wen was, after all, the wisest of men."
